OL,3,C'Callous' fraudster who tricked
OL,4,Cgrieving relatives paying for funerals
OL,5,Cjailed
OL,7,FHe took almost a thousand pounds from
OL,8,Fhis back pocket and handed it over.
OL,9,FDrinkwater put his coat on, left, and
OL,10,Fnever returned.
OL,12,FIn the following months, when the
OL,13,Ffuneral directors called customers to
OL,14,Fsettle their balances, they were told
OL,15,Fthey had already done so - to
OL,16,FDrinkwater.
OL,18,FIn some cases, Drinkwater had
OL,19,Ffraudulently forged customer
OL,20,Fsignatures on paperwork.
